OL,6,FIt is also believed the burying place
OL,7,Fmay not be the only one in Royton
OL,8,FCemetery.
OL,10,FThe councillors say there was one in
OL,11,Fthe Catholic area, one in the non-
OL,12,Fconformist area, and one in the C of E
OL,13,Fsection.
OL,15,FThe Royton Independents are urging
OL,16,FOldham Borough Council to "recognise
OL,17,Fthe loss and suffering in the past and
OL,18,Fpresent."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
